<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 07-16-02 - Corrected Calibration Procedure for Optional Instrument Cluster Compass</stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi071602" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>07-16-02</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>August 2007</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>Cab</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Corrected Calibration Procedure for Optional Instrument Cluster Compass</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <distribution dealer="yes" fleet="yes" bodybuilder="no" isis_cd="yes"/>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>4100</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>4300</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>4400</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>7300</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>7400</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>7500</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>7600</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>7700</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>8500</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>8600</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>ProStar</truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>The calibration procedure for the optional instrument cluster compass is incorrect as printed in
                    the current Operator's Manuals. The following procedure should be followed for compass calibration.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="8">
            <title>Instrument Cluster compass Calibration</title>
            <svcprocinfo>
                <specpara>
                    <warning>
                        <para>To avoid personal injury or death, pull vehicle off roadway and away from all other
                            traffic before performing the following procedure.
                        </para>
                    </warning>
                </specpara>
                <para>All new vehicles must have an initial compass calibration performed. In addition, if the NO CAL
                    message is displayed, the compass will need to be calibrated. If the compass headings become
                    noticeably incorrect, the compass may need to be recalibrated or the Declination Zone may need to be
                    reset to agree with the current geographic location (refer to the zone map in the Operators Manual).
                    Both procedures are listed below and must be followed exactly to insure proper calibration of the
                    compass.
                </para>
            </svcprocinfo>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>Compass Calibration Procedure</title>
                <para>To begin the compass calibration procedure, stop the vehicle in an area large enough to permit
                    driving in complete circles and perform the following steps:
                </para>
                <table id="t0716021" tblwidth="pg-wide" frame="all">
                    <title>Compass Calibration Procedure</title>
                    <tgroup cols="3">
                        <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="0.33*"/>
                        <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.85*"/>
                        <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="0.82*"/>
                        <thead>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center">
                                    <para>Step</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Procedure</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry align="center">
                                    <para>Displayed Message</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center">
                                    <para>1</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Select Quadrant 2 on the display by turning the display control either
                                        clockwise or counter-clockwise.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry></entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center">
                                    <para>2</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Select the Calibrate Compass message by pressing and releasing the display
                                        control until this message appears.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g0716021.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                                             scalefitwidth="112px" scalefitheight="72px"/>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center">
                                    <para>3</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Press and hold the display control until the End Calibration message is
                                        displayed.
                                    </para>
                                    <para>
                                        <emph type="bold">NOTE:</emph>
                                        The following steps (4 through 6) must be completed within 3 minutes to lock-in
                                        the new calibration.
                                        <emph type="boldital">Do not press the display control or turn the key off until
                                            these steps are completed or the calibration process will be cancelled.
                                        </emph>
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g0716022.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                                             scalefitwidth="112px" scalefitheight="72px"/>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center">
                                    <para>4</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Immediately following the End Calibration message being displayed, drive the
                                        vehicle in 3 complete circles (during this time the compass display will go
                                        blank or have dashed lines present).
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g0716023.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                                             scalefitwidth="112px" scalefitheight="72px"/>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center">
                                    <para>5</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Stop the vehicle, place the transmission in Neutral and apply the Park Brake.
                                        The End Calibration message should reappear on the display.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g0716022.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                                             scalefitwidth="112px" scalefitheight="72px"/>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center">
                                    <para>6</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Push and
                                        <emph type="boldital">hold</emph>
                                        the display control (failure to hold the control will cancel the calibration
                                        procedure) until the End Calibration message disappears. The calibration should
                                        now be complete.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry></entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                    </tgroup>
                </table>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>If the compass has been recalibrated, the Declination Zone may also need to be reset.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </svcsubproc>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>Declination Zone Set Procedure</title>
                <para>The declination zone number is used to account for the vehicle's geographic operating area and
                    must be set correctly for the compass to display accurate headings.
                </para>
                <para>For vehicles that regularly operate coast-to-coast or in several different declination zones,
                    either choose a declination zone in the geographic center of the vehicle's operating area, or change
                    the declination zone daily to match the present declination zone.
                </para>
                <para>To begin the declination zone set procedure, the vehicle must be stopped. Refer to Zone Map 1 in
                    the Operator's Manual for determining the proper declination zone number.
                </para>
                <table id="t0716022" tblwidth="pg-wide" frame="all">
                    <title>Declination Zone Set Procedure</title>
                    <tgroup cols="3">
                        <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="0.33*"/>
                        <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.86*"/>
                        <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="0.80*"/>
                        <thead>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center">
                                    <para>Step</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Procedure</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry align="center">
                                    <para>Displayed Message</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center">
                                    <para>1</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Select Quadrant 2 on the display by turning the display control either
                                        clockwise or counter-clockwise.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry></entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center">
                                    <para>2</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Select the Compass Declination message by pressing and releasing the display
                                        control until this message appears.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g0716024.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                                             scalefitwidth="112px" scalefitheight="72px"/>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center">
                                    <para>3</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Press and hold the display control until a zone number (0 &#8722; 10) is
                                        displayed.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g0716025.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                                             scalefitwidth="112px" scalefitheight="72px"/>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center">
                                    <para>4</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Turn the display control clockwise or counter-clockwise until the desired zone
                                        is displayed. Refer to Zone Map 1 to determine the proper number for the current
                                        geographic location.
                                    </para>
                                    <para>
                                        <emph type="bold">NOTE:</emph>
                                        If no zone number is selected within 15 seconds, the display will return to the
                                        Compass Declination message.
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g0716026.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                                             scalefitwidth="112px" scalefitheight="72px"/>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry align="center">
                                    <para>5</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>Press and hold the display control until the Compass Declination message
                                        appears (this indicates that the new declination zone number has been programmed
                                        into the compass).
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g0716024.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                                             scalefitwidth="112px" scalefitheight="72px"/>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                    </tgroup>
                </table>
            </svcsubproc>
        </svcproc>
    </tsi>
</isis>
